review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

A prism has two identical faces. It is named for its cross-section.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

When a pair of lines is cut by a transversal, special angles are formed. When the pair of lines is parallel, the alternate angles are equal, the corresponding angles are equal and the co-interior angles are supplementary. Vertically opposite angles are equal,
so y = x.

success.question_text: When the pattern is completed, which square will not be shaded?

stimulus_1.text: This pattern is symmetrical about the two lines l and m.

review_3.column_1_text:
Of the options, the square that is not shaded is F9.

Tip

If a design is reflected about a line, the line will be an axis of symmetry.

stimulus_1.text: The cone is cut parallel to the base as shown in the diagram.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

A cross-section can be thought of as a slice of a solid.

Tip

If a quadrilateral has both pairs of opposite sides parallel, it is a parallelogram. If a quadrilateral has both pair of opposite sides equal, it is a parallelogram. If a quadrilateral has one pair of opposite sides equal and parallel, it is a parallelogram.

Tip

An acute-angled triangle has all its angles acute. An obtuse-angled triangle has one angle that is obtuse. A scalene triangle has no equal sides and no equal angles. An isosceles triangle has two equal sides and two equal angles.

success.question_text: When the paper is unfolded, what will it look like?

stimulus_1.text: Sue folded a piece of paper in half and then half again. She then cut a piece from the folded corner as shown in the diagram.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Actually folding a piece of paper is a good way to investigate properties of symmetry.

success.question_text: Which solid has seven faces and 12 edges?

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

Consider each option:

  • A hexagonal pyramid has seven faces and 12 edges.
  • A hexagonal prism has eight faces and 18 edges.
  • A pentagonal pyramid has six faces and 10 edges.
  • A pentagonal prism has seven faces and 15 edges.

The solid that has seven faces and 12 edges is a hexagonal pyramid.

review_2.column_1_text:
Tip

For any solid, the number of faces plus the number of vertices is always two more than the number of edges.

success.question_text:
Hannah measures the length of the drawing and finds that it is 12 cm.

What scale has been used?

stimulus_1.text: The diagram shows a scale drawing of a yard.

review_3.column_1_text:
12 cm represents 48 m.

1 cm represents 4 m.

1 cm represents 400 cm.

The scale is 1:400.

Tip

The scale in a scale drawing must use the same units if written as a ratio.

success.question_text: Which two words can be placed in the spaces to make the statement correct?

stimulus_1.text: ‘In __________ figures, the corresponding sides must be __________ .’

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

In similar figures, the corresponding sides must be in proportion. They need not be equal or parallel.

In congruent figures, the corresponding sides must be equal. They need not be parallel.

The correct words are ‘congruent’ and ‘equal’.

Tip

Congruent figures are exactly the same size and exactly the same shape. Similar figures are the same shape but not necessarily the same size.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Take time to think before answering a question. Not all the information might be relevant. For example, in this question it didn’t matter that the two lines were parallel.

success.question_text:
The two triangles are joined along the hypotenuses to make a quadrilateral.

Which best describes the quadrilateral formed?

stimulus_1.text: These two congruent triangles are both right-angled and isosceles.

review_3.column_1_text:
The quadrilateral has four equal sides so it is a rhombus.

It has one angle a right angle so it is a square.

Tip

Make sure you understand the definitions of the special quadrilaterals. For example, a rhombus that has one angle that is a right angle must be a square. If one angle is a right angle, it does not mean only one. It means that if that angle is a right angle then the shape is a square and all the other angles must be 90° as well.

choice_1.label: A quadrilateral but not a parallelogram

choice_2.label: A parallelogram but not a rhombus

choice_3.label: A rhombus but not a square

success.question_text: What is growing both east of the cauliflower and south of the chokos?

stimulus_1.text: Souad’s garden is divided into plots where she grows many different types of vegetables.

review_3.column_1_text:
The vegetables growing east of the cauliflower are potatoes, tomatoes, zucchinis and lettuce.

The vegetables growing south of the chokos are lettuce, capsicums, beans and spinach.

The vegetable that is growing both east of the cauliflowers and south of the chokos is lettuce.

Tip

Look carefully at plans and maps. Although north is usually found at the top of the page it is not always the case.

review_6.column_1_text:
Tip

Perpendicular lines meet at right angles.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

The exterior angle of a triangle is equal to the sum of the interior opposite angles.

success.question_text:
Through how many degrees could the blue shape be rotated in a clockwise direction
to map onto the yellow shape?

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Read the question carefully. For example, in this question the blue shape could map onto the yellow under a rotation of 120° but in an anticlockwise direction.
